PESTE DES PETITS RUMINANTS - BHUTAN: (CHHUKHA) GOAT, OIE
********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 18 Jul 2014
Source: OIE WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database) Disease Information 2014; 27(30) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=15654


Peste des petits ruminants, Bhutan
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 18 Jul 2014 from Dr. Tashi Samdup, Director, Ministry of Agriculture, Department of Livestock and Forests, Thimphu, Bhutan

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 8 Jul 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 14 Jul 2014
Report date: 18 Jul 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 18 Jul 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Peste des petits ruminants virus
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Bjabcho, Chhukha, Chhukha
Date of start of the outbreak: 8 Jul 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Goats / 27 / 27 / 7 / 0 / 0
Affected population: The goats were rescued from slaughter and kept in an enclosed shelter away from human habitation.
Outbreak statistics:
Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost (Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter)
100 percent / 25.93 percent / 25.93 percent / 25.93 percent

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Introduction of new live animals, Illegal movement of animals

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country, disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), dipping/spraying, vaccination prohibited, treatment of affected animals (antimicrobials/vitamins)
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Centre for Animal Health (national laboratory) / Goat / Antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 14 Jul 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to information found in their annual report (January to December 2013) submitted to the OIE, Bhutan reported 2 outbreaks of peste des petits ruminants (PPR) in the Chhukha district, where the affected species were also goats (http://tinyurl.com/km2qtat; go to Section 3 of the report, named "Detailed quantitative information for OIE-listed diseases/infections present", to see detailed information on these outbreaks).

A disease outbreak map on PPR from January to July 2014 is available at http://tinyurl.com/pyltp8t. To view the region of interest and outbreak information in greater detail, click on the map to zoom in. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2622379,12668.]
